text: Suzanne "Sue" Twelftree (12 August 1956 - 16 April 2019) was an Australian wheelchair tennis player and Paralympic powerlifter. She was born in Wallaroo, South Australia. At the 2000 Summer Paralympics in Sydney, she competed in the Women's up to 48 kg powerlifting and finished ninth. Twelftree died on 16 April 2019 in Adelaide, South Australia, at the age of 62. ==References== ==Other websites== * Suzanne Twelftree ITF profile Category:1956 births Category:2019 deaths Category:Australian tennis players Category:Australian paralympic competitors Category:Sportspeople from South Australia
